:
When I spoke to the boss...

03:52.933 --> 03:54.535
Fukyama.

03:54.568 --> 03:59.172
He said the plan was to kill
Oliver when we find him.

04:05.946 --> 04:09.950
Let's make sure
we find him first.

04:12.620 --> 04:14.254
DAVID:
Is he-- sh-she...

04:14.288 --> 04:15.556
are they...

04:15.589 --> 04:16.990
I don't know what to call them.

04:17.024 --> 04:19.593
We call them Vermillion.

04:19.627 --> 04:22.095
DAVID:
Are they mutants?

04:22.129 --> 04:24.732
Androids, I think.

04:24.765 --> 04:28.469
Synthetic, artificial.

04:30.704 --> 04:32.506
I'll be honest.

04:32.540 --> 04:35.108
They made me nervous at first.

04:35.142 --> 04:38.479
But now I find them...

04:38.512 --> 04:39.680
soothing.

04:39.713 --> 04:41.682
They've got no memories for me.

04:41.715 --> 04:44.518
Just data.

04:44.552 --> 04:47.755
How many are there?

04:47.788 --> 04:49.790
No one knows.

04:51.692 --> 04:53.661
All right, stop the truck!

04:53.694 --> 04:55.295
SYD:
Why?

04:56.897 --> 04:58.866
We're here.

05:12.312 --> 05:14.348
VERMILLION 1:
Lead us.

05:23.056 --> 05:25.058
PTONOMY:
What is that?

05:28.862 --> 05:30.531
Syd.

05:30.564 --> 05:33.401
VERMILLION 2: Chance the object
is explosive in nature...

05:33.434 --> 05:35.869
VERMILLION 3:
27%.

06:04.965 --> 06:07.435
DAVID:
What's wrong?

06:07.468 --> 06:08.936
SYD:
Nothing.

06:08.969 --> 06:10.370
Just your asshole parasite

06:10.404 --> 06:12.406
messing with my head.

06:13.774 --> 06:15.943
PTONOMY:
Stay alert.

06:15.976 --> 06:17.077
This feels like a trap.

06:17.110 --> 06:18.178
No, they're gone.

06:18.211 --> 06:19.246
VERMILLION 2:
An error?

06:19.279 --> 06:20.714
DAVID:
Trick.

06:20.748 --> 06:23.717
He knew I was looking,
showed me this spot,

06:23.751 --> 06:25.619
-and then left.
-PTONOMY: So, if Oliver's

06:25.653 --> 06:28.456
not here, where is he?

